title: Hunter Biden's savage message to 'motherf****r' Donald Trump's attacks on Joe Biden
description: Former US President Joe Biden’s son Hunter has brutally unleashed on US President Donald Trump.  In an interview with host Joshua Rubin on the ‘Wide Awake’ podcast, Hunter described President Trump’s contentious attacks on his father.  Hunter claimed Trump was “obsessed” with Joe Biden because he “beat him by 7.5 million votes” in 2020.  In the interview, Rubin questioned Hunter on whether both sides needed to calm down in regards to extremism, to which Hunter urged Democrats to “turn the temperature up”.  Hunter Biden urged for less violence, but said Democrats and the left need to “speak truth to power”.

title: ‘102 minutes I’ll never get back’: New York Times’ anti-feminism podcast slandered
description: Sky News contributor Jaimee Rogers says women have certainly “not ruined the workforce” after the New York Times published an article arguing “wokeism” and “feminism” have ruined the workplace.  “I don’t think that women have ruined the workforce in any way, shape or form,” Ms Rogers said.  “They have brought in things like equal pay and maternity leave.  “Feminism just changed the way we do business.  “We now need to move with the times.”

title: ‘Don’t mess with Trump’: UK public ‘celebrate’ after US President exposes BBC’s leftist bias
description: TalkTV host Mark Dolan claims the leftist group at the BBC has been “outed” and exposed by US President Donald Trump following revelations the UK national broadcaster doctored one of his speeches.  “In Britain, we are celebrating the fact that at last, we have accountability for an organisation that we are obliged to pay a compulsory tax for just to own a TV,” he told Sky News host James Macpherson.  “You don’t mess with Trump. You do so at your peril. He’s very angry about this.”  Mr Dolan’s remarks come as US President Donald Trump plans to sue the BBC despite the British broadcaster apologising for an edit of a speech from 2021.  The US President says he will be looking at anything between $1-5 billion in damages.

title: ‘He’s got less than a year’: ‘Struggling’ Keir Starmer on ‘borrowed time’ amid economic failures
description: TalkTV host Mark Dolan claims UK Prime Minister Keir Starmer is on “borrowed time” as the economy struggles.  “The guy is struggling ... what you got is a perfect storm of his political ineptitude and the raw numbers,” he told Sky News host James Macpherson.  “I do think he’s on borrowed time.  “He’s got less than a year.”

title: New York Times article sparks worldwide controversy and debate
description: Broadcaster Kel Richards says he doesn’t see a “problem” with women in the workforce.  This comes after the New York Times published an article called ‘Did Women Ruin the Workplace?’, which sparked controversy.   “I really couldn’t in the end grasp a solid point they were getting at,” Mr Richards said.  “In my lifetime, I’ve seen the profession of journalism feminised.   “You just work with people who have got decent brains.”

title: ‘Divisions’ in the Republican Party begin to appear amid Trump- Taylor Greene feud
description: Former White House chief of staff Mick Mulvaney discusses how the relationship between US President Donald Trump and Republican Congresswoman Marjorie Taylor Greene has “fallen apart”.  “It’s very interesting to see the divisions that are now cropping up within the Republican Party,” he told Sky News Australia.  Ms Mulvaney’s remarks come as the pair have been trading blows after the congresswoman backed a push to release Justice Department files linked to sex offender Jeffrey Epstein.

title: ‘You are the worst’: Donald Trump brutally blasts reporter for interrupting him
description: US President Donald Trump has blasted a reporter for interrupting him while he was responding to media questions on Sunday, local time.  “Will you let me finish my statement? You are the worst,” he said.  “You’re with Bloomberg, right? You are the worst. I don’t know why they even have you.”

title: ‘Major consequences’: Albanese called out for lying about net zero
description: Liberal Senator Sarah Henderson expresses strong support for Opposition Leader Sussan Ley's leadership, emphasising the consequences of the Prime Minister's misleading claims regarding power prices and energy policy.  “There are major consequences for this Prime Minister lying,” Ms Henderson told Sky News Australia.  “I absolutely back her for getting out and fighting for all Australians.  “This net zero rubbish is an ideology that has not worked.”

title: Trump threatens the BBC with mammoth $5 billion lawsuit as Brits support the takedown
description: Donald Trump wants to take down the BBC.    Yes, the British broadcaster is feeling the wrath of the President of the United States after it was revealed that they edited a speech he gave about January 6.

title: ‘I don’t think anybody cares about her’: Trump unleashes on Marjorie 'traitor' Greene amid feud
description: US President Donald Trump has again hit out at Republican Congresswoman Marjorie Taylor Greene while responding to reporters’ questions on Sunday, local time.  “Marjorie Traitor Greene. I don’t think her life is in danger,” he said.  “Frankly, I don’t think anybody cares about her.”

title: Democrats’ use of Epstein files to target Trump reflects ‘very badly’ on party
description: Political analyst Joe Siracusa claims the Democrats’ use of the Epstein files to target US President Donald Trump reflects “very badly” on the party.  “The Democrats have been chasing this, and of course, it’s going to reflect very badly on Democrats,” Mr Siracusa said.  “The Democrats haven’t looked very good about this … the Democrats have prolonged a 43-day shutdown, causing Americans to suffer a great deal.  “The Democrats have handled this poorly.”

title: ‘Me Too has gone way too far’: Movement accused of ‘ruining the fun’ for others
description: Former Liberal senator Hollie Hughes says the Me Too movement has “ruined” other people’s fun.  “The Me Too movement has gone way, way, way too far,” Ms Hughes said.  “It’s taken a lot of the fun out of the world because no one can say anything nice to anyone anymore without it being completely misinterpreted.”

title: Three moderates allegedly pushing Andrew Hastie to go up against Sussan Ley
description: Sky News Political Editor Andrew Clennell addresses claims MP Andrew Hastie faces pressure from moderates, including Tim Wilson, Andrew Bragg, and Dave Sharma, to challenge Opposition Leader Sussan Ley for the party leadership.  “Three moderates are said to have been in a breakaway position and prepared to back Andrew Hastie basically almost goading Andrew Hastie to run next week,” Mr Clennell told Sky News Australia.  “An overwhelming majority of our moderate colleagues, not the entire faction, continue to strongly support Sussan’s leadership.  “He has no intention of running next week.”

title: Liz Truss backs Trump suing the 'biased' BBC calling for the broadcaster to be 'defunded'
description: Former UK prime minister Liz Truss has thrown her support behind US President Donald Trump's legal action against the BBC.  Truss claimed the BBC has "lied, cheated and fiddled with footage" not only in the case of Trump, but in other key issues affecting Britain.  The former prime minister blasted the BBC over a misleading edit of the president's speech, which aired on the broadcaster's Investigative documentary series 'Panorama'.  The former prime minister asserted that the taxpayer-funded broadcaster is always "biased" towards the left.  Truss goes on to say an apology from the BBC to Trump is not enough, claiming they have painted a "false picture" of the president.  The former prime minister called for the broadcaster to be "defunded".

title: Newly released email suggests Andrew had a ‘massage’ at Ghislaine Maxwell’s home
description: An email released from the Jeffrey Epstein files suggests Andrew Mountbatten-Windsor had a “massage” at Ghislaine Maxwell’s house.  The revelations were made from a 2015 email.  In the email, she told Mr Epstein she had to distance herself from him in a statement, writing: ‘And they need me to say I was not aware of massage w/andrew in my house’.  More than 20,000 pages of emails and other evidence were released earlier this week.
